  1. Table of the RIVERS crossed with the SPECIES of fish.

Task 6: Boxplot

  1. Boxplot of the variable DDT
boxplot(ddt$DDT, 
        main = "Boxplot of DDT",
        xlab = "dbl",
        ylab = "DDT", 
        col = "Orange",
        border = "brown",
        horizontal = TRUE,
        notch = TRUE
)

  1. Boxplot of the variable WEIGHT
boxplot(ddt$WEIGHT, 
        main = "Boxplot of WEIGHT",
        xlab = "weight unit",
        ylab = "WEIGHT", 
        col = "Orange",
        border = "brown",
        horizontal = TRUE,
        notch = TRUE
)

  1. Boxplot of the variable LENGTH
boxplot(ddt$LENGTH, 
        main = "Boxplot of LENGTH",
        xlab = "Length unit",
        ylab = "LENGTH", 
        col = "Orange",
        border = "brown",
        horizontal = TRUE,
        notch = TRUE
)

Task 7: Coplot

  1. Coplot of LENGTH Vs WEIGHT given RIVER
coplot(LENGTH ~ WEIGHT | RIVER, 
       data=ddt, 
       col = with(ddt, ifelse (SPECIES == "CCATFISH", "Pink",
                  ifelse(SPECIES == "SMBUFFALO", "Green", "Orange"))))

  1. Coplot of DDT vs WEIGHT given SPECIES
coplot(DDT ~ WEIGHT | SPECIES, data = ddt)

Task 8: ggplot: Box, Violin, Scatter

  1. ggplot: Boxplot for WEIGHT vs SPECIES
library(ggplot2)
ggplot(ddt, ggplot2::aes(x=SPECIES, y=WEIGHT)) + geom_boxplot(aes(fill=RIVER)) + ggtitle("Yangzom Dolma")

b. ggplot: Violin Plot for LENGTH vs RIVER

print(ggplot(ddt, aes(x=RIVER, y = LENGTH)) + geom_violin(aes(fill =SPECIES)) + ggtitle("Yangzom Dolma"))

c.ggplot: Scatter Plot for LENGTH vs WEIGHT

ggsc = ggplot(ddt, aes(x= WEIGHT, y = LENGTH))

ggsc = ggsc + geom_point(aes(color = SPECIES)) + ggtitle("Yangzom Dolma")

print(ggsc)
